description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Pharmacy Assistant&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Band 2 / 3 (dependent on relevant qualification)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Band 2 Salary - £18,005 - £19,337 per annum&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Band 3 Salary - £19,737 - £21,142 per annum&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We’re looking for enthusiastic people to join our team and help us to continue the development of a range of clinical pharmacy services throughout the hospital.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Your main responsibilities in this post will be to assist in the dispensing and supply of medicines for patients at Torbay Hospital, and undertake related ward-based duties including management of stocks in the hospital.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Candidates should possess a good general standard of education and have excellent communication and organisational skills. Whilst previous experience of hospital pharmacy would be an advantage, we will provide a comprehensive training and development programme to enable you to undertake your new role. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information, please telephone Dan Dodwell (Clinical Technician Manager) on 01803-655285/email &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;d.dodwell@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;, or Sally Rowe (Dispensary Manager) on 01803-655905/email &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;sally.rowe2@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
